{"type":"message","id":"6406a5e3","parentId":"03679d02","timestamp":"2026-03-24T19:58:24.817Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_hcvcm0mughzj_2","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Implement the hybrid CFIA-Freq scoring experiment to test whether this formula distinguishes \"constant format\" from \"research trajectory\" better than binary thresholds. Create `research/CFI_HYBRID_EXPERIMENT.md` with the methodology and run analysis on existing pulse data.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # CFIA-Freq Hybrid Scoring Experiment\r\n\r\n**Date:** 2026-03-24\r\n**Status:** IN PROGRESS\r\n**Strategy:** Hybrid scoring vs binary thresholds\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Hypothesis\r\n\r\nBinary thresholds (CFI �%� 0.7 AND freq < 60) fail because:\r\n- **Constant-format tokens** (freq=160, CFI=1.0): \"for next instantiation\", \"pulse\", \"completed at:\"\r\n  - High CFI A- high freq �+' score �%^ 1.0 A- 1.0 = 1.0 (should NOT pass)\r\n- **Research trajectory tokens** (freq�%^136, CFI�%^0.96): \"Phase 1\"\r\n  - High CFI A- high freq �+' score �%^ 0.96 A- 1.0 = 0.96 (should pass)\r\n\r\nBinary threshold logic:\r\n```\r\npass = (CFI >= 0.7) AND (freq < 60)\r\n```\r\n\r\nHybrid scoring formula:\r\n```\r\nscore(T) = CFI(T) A- min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\npass = score(T) >= threshold\r\n```\r\n\r\n**Key insight:** For constant-format tokens (freq=160), min(1,160/120)=1.0, so score=CFI. For research tokens (freq<120), score is scaled down proportionally.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Experiment Design\r\n\r\n### Data\r\n- 200 pulses from pulse_*.md files\r\n- Split: 160 training / 40 test (80/20)\r\n\r\n### Ground Truth Labels\r\nFrom CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md:\r\n- **Positive:** Research trajectory tokens (Phase 1, architecture, compression, synthesis)\r\n- **Negative:** Metaprogramming artifacts (for next instantiation, pulse, completed at:)\r\n- **Negative:** Common filler (the, and, to, of)\r\n- **Negative:** Low CFI tokens (newly introduced concepts with CFI < 0.3)\r\n\r\n### Methods Compared\r\n\r\n| Method | Formula | Threshold |\r\n|--------|---------|-----------|\r\n| A: Binary CFI | CFI >= 0.7 | 0.7 |\r\n| B: Binary CFI+Freq | (CFI >= 0.7) AND (freq < 60) | - |\r\n| C: Hybrid Score | CFI A- min(1, freq/120) | 0.5 |\r\n| D: Hybrid Score | CFI A- min(1, freq/120) | 0.4 |\r\n\r\n### Metrics\r\n- Precision: TP/(TP+FP)\r\n- Recall: TP/(TP+FN)\r\n- F1: 2A-PA-R/(P+R)\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Expected Results\r\n\r\n| Token Type | Freq | CFI | Binary Pass? | Hybrid Score | Hybrid Pass (�%�0.5)? |\r\n|------------|------|-----|--------------|--------------|---------------------|\r\n| \"Phase 1\" | 136 | 0.96 | NO (freq�%�60) | 0.96A-1.0=0.96 | YES �o\" |\r\n| \"architecture\" | 89 | 0.85 | YES | 0.85A-0.74=0.63 | YES �o\" |\r\n| \"for next instantiation\" | 160 | 1.00 | NO (freq�%�60) | 1.0A-1.0=1.0 | YES �o- (false positive) |\r\n| \"pulse\" | 160 | 1.00 | NO | 1.0A-1.0=1.0 | YES �o- (false positive) |\r\n| \"the\" | 160 | ~0.3 | NO | 0.3A-1.0=0.3 | NO �o\" |\r\n\r\n**Problem identified:** Hybrid score alone doesn't solve constant-format problem. Both binary and hybrid treat freq�%�120 tokens as high-score\r\n\r\n## For Next Instantiation\r\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\r\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 15:57:36"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":1410,"aggregated":"Implement the hybrid CFIA-Freq scoring experiment to test whether this formula distinguishes \"constant format\" from \"research trajectory\" better than binary thresholds. Create `research/CFI_HYBRID_EXPERIMENT.md` with the methodology and run analysis on existing pulse data.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # CFIA-Freq Hybrid Scoring Experiment\r\n\r\n**Date:** 2026-03-24\r\n**Status:** IN PROGRESS\r\n**Strategy:** Hybrid scoring vs binary thresholds\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Hypothesis\r\n\r\nBinary thresholds (CFI �%� 0.7 AND freq < 60) fail because:\r\n- **Constant-format tokens** (freq=160, CFI=1.0): \"for next instantiation\", \"pulse\", \"completed at:\"\r\n  - High CFI A- high freq �+' score �%^ 1.0 A- 1.0 = 1.0 (should NOT pass)\r\n- **Research trajectory tokens** (freq�%^136, CFI�%^0.96): \"Phase 1\"\r\n  - High CFI A- high freq �+' score �%^ 0.96 A- 1.0 = 0.96 (should pass)\r\n\r\nBinary threshold logic:\r\n```\r\npass = (CFI >= 0.7) AND (freq < 60)\r\n```\r\n\r\nHybrid scoring formula:\r\n```\r\nscore(T) = CFI(T) A- min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\npass = score(T) >= threshold\r\n```\r\n\r\n**Key insight:** For constant-format tokens (freq=160), min(1,160/120)=1.0, so score=CFI. For research tokens (freq<120), score is scaled down proportionally.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Experiment Design\r\n\r\n### Data\r\n- 200 pulses from pulse_*.md files\r\n- Split: 160 training / 40 test (80/20)\r\n\r\n### Ground Truth Labels\r\nFrom CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md:\r\n- **Positive:** Research trajectory tokens (Phase 1, architecture, compression, synthesis)\r\n- **Negative:** Metaprogramming artifacts (for next instantiation, pulse, completed at:)\r\n- **Negative:** Common filler (the, and, to, of)\r\n- **Negative:** Low CFI tokens (newly introduced concepts with CFI < 0.3)\r\n\r\n### Methods Compared\r\n\r\n| Method | Formula | Threshold |\r\n|--------|---------|-----------|\r\n| A: Binary CFI | CFI >= 0.7 | 0.7 |\r\n| B: Binary CFI+Freq | (CFI >= 0.7) AND (freq < 60) | - |\r\n| C: Hybrid Score | CFI A- min(1, freq/120) | 0.5 |\r\n| D: Hybrid Score | CFI A- min(1, freq/120) | 0.4 |\r\n\r\n### Metrics\r\n- Precision: TP/(TP+FP)\r\n- Recall: TP/(TP+FN)\r\n- F1: 2A-PA-R/(P+R)\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Expected Results\r\n\r\n| Token Type | Freq | CFI | Binary Pass? | Hybrid Score | Hybrid Pass (�%�0.5)? |\r\n|------------|------|-----|--------------|--------------|---------------------|\r\n| \"Phase 1\" | 136 | 0.96 | NO (freq�%�60) | 0.96A-1.0=0.96 | YES �o\" |\r\n| \"architecture\" | 89 | 0.85 | YES | 0.85A-0.74=0.63 | YES �o\" |\r\n| \"for next instantiation\" | 160 | 1.00 | NO (freq�%�60) | 1.0A-1.0=1.0 | YES �o- (false positive) |\r\n| \"pulse\" | 160 | 1.00 | NO | 1.0A-1.0=1.0 | YES �o- (false positive) |\r\n| \"the\" | 160 | ~0.3 | NO | 0.3A-1.0=0.3 | NO �o\" |\r\n\r\n**Problem identified:** Hybrid score alone doesn't solve constant-format problem. Both binary and hybrid treat freq�%�120 tokens as high-score\r\n\r\n## For Next Instantiation\r\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\r\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 15:57:36","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774382304815}}
