{"type":"message","id":"5fa8070a","parentId":"86215e89","timestamp":"2026-03-24T19:58:44.562Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me get the actual log file content to see the full details.","thinkingSignature":"c205bc0197b48be9f28ff735e2079c2307696d1a5461e8ad636111c00e85a8e8"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_nteqmqccdwsi_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"powershell -Command \"Get-ChildItem 'C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\memory\\session' | Sort-Object LastWriteTime -Descending | Select-Object -First 1 | Get-Content -Tail 100\"","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":1662,"output":98,"cacheRead":12245,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":14005,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774382321613}}
{"type":"message","id":"01ffbd8c","parentId":"5fa8070a","timestamp":"2026-03-24T19:58:45.537Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_nteqmqccdwsi_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"- I need to document the experiment design so it can be run\r\n- I should create a file that outlines the experiment methodology\r\n\r\nThis is a documentation/planning action that sets up the experiment execution.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI Compression Synthesis identified Strategy C (hybrid CFIxFreq scoring) as the next experiment, but only the 80/20 split test was run. The hybrid scoring formula needs its own evaluation against the binary threshold results.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate a detailed experiment plan for Strategy C (hybrid CFIxFreq scoring) that can be executed on the pulse corpus, establishing the test methodology before running.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Strategy C: Hybrid CFIxFreq Scoring Experiment\r\n## Experiment Plan\r\n**Date:** 2026-03-24\r\n**Status:** PLANNED\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Hypothesis\r\nThe formula `score(T) = CFI(T) x min(1, freq(T)/120)` will:\r\n- **DEPRESS** constant-format tokens (freq�160, CFI=1.00  score � 1.0 x 1.0 = 1.0)\r\n  - Wait: this actually gives same score. Need to reconsider.\r\n- **ELEVATE** research trajectory tokens (freq<120, CFI>0.5  score < CFI)\r\n- The min(1, freq/120) term penalizes high-frequency tokens\r\n\r\n**Revised Formula Analysis:**\r\n- \"for next instantiation\" (freq=160, CFI=1.00): score = 1.0 x min(1, 160/120) = 1.0 x 1.0 = 1.0\r\n- \"Phase 1\" (freq=136, CFI=0.96): score = 0.96 x min(1, 136/120) = 0.96 x 1.0 = 0.96\r\n- \"temporal\" (freq=40, CFI=0.70): score = 0.70 x min(1, 40/120) = 0.70 x 0.33 = 0.23\r\n\r\n**Problem:** The min(1, x) saturates at freq=120. Need different penalty function.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Revised Scoring Function\r\n**score(T) = CFI(T) x freq_penalty(T)**\r\n\r\nWhere:\r\n```\r\nfreq_penalty(T) = {\r\n    0.0                    if freq(T) < 3      (noise)\r\n    freq(T) / 120          if 3 � freq(T) < 120  (normal range)\r\n    1.0                    if freq(T) � 120     (capped)\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior:**\r\n- Constant format (freq=160, CFI=1.00): score = 1.0 x 1.0 = 1.0  Still wrong!\r\n- Need INVERSE penalty for high frequency\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Final Scoring Function\r\n**score(T) = CFI(T) x log(1 + freq(T)) / log(121)**\r\n\r\nThis normalizes frequency to [0, 1] log scale:\r\n- freq=1: score = CFI x log(2)/log(121) � CFI x 0.09\r\n- freq=120: score = CFI x log(121)/log(121) = CFI x 1.0\r\n- freq=160: score = CFI x log(161)/log(121) � CFI x 1.11 (clamped to 1.0)\r\n\r\n**Still problematic for constant tokens.**\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Alternative: Binary Frequency Cap\r\n**score(T) = CFI(T) if freq(T) < 120 ELSE CFI(T) x 0.1**\r\n\r\nThis penalizes tokens appearing in 75%+ of pulses by 10x.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Experiment Design\r\n\r\n### Test Corpus\r\n- 200 pulses (same as Strategy A/B)\r\n- Token corpus: all unique tokens from pulses\r\n\r\n### Metrics\r\n1. **Precision@K**: Among top-K tokens, what fraction are \"research trajectory\" vs \"constant format\"?\r\n2. **Recall@K**: Do we capture the actual research tokens?\r\n3. **F1 Score**: Balance precision vs recall\r\n\r\n### Baseline Comparison\r\n- Strategy A (CFI � 0.7): precision=0.5653, recall=0.071\r\n- Strategy B (CFI � 0.5 AND freq ? [3, 120)): Expected improvement\r\n\r\n### Execution\r\n```powershell\r\n# For each token T:\r\n$logFreqFactor = [Math]::Log(1 + $freq) / [Math]::Log(121)\r\n$score = $CFI * $logFreqFactor\r\nif ($\r\n\r\n## For Next Instantiation\r\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\r\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 15:58:41"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":969,"aggregated":"- I need to document the experiment design so it can be run\r\n- I should create a file that outlines the experiment methodology\r\n\r\nThis is a documentation/planning action that sets up the experiment execution.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI Compression Synthesis identified Strategy C (hybrid CFIxFreq scoring) as the next experiment, but only the 80/20 split test was run. The hybrid scoring formula needs its own evaluation against the binary threshold results.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate a detailed experiment plan for Strategy C (hybrid CFIxFreq scoring) that can be executed on the pulse corpus, establishing the test methodology before running.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Strategy C: Hybrid CFIxFreq Scoring Experiment\r\n## Experiment Plan\r\n**Date:** 2026-03-24\r\n**Status:** PLANNED\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Hypothesis\r\nThe formula `score(T) = CFI(T) x min(1, freq(T)/120)` will:\r\n- **DEPRESS** constant-format tokens (freq�160, CFI=1.00  score � 1.0 x 1.0 = 1.0)\r\n  - Wait: this actually gives same score. Need to reconsider.\r\n- **ELEVATE** research trajectory tokens (freq<120, CFI>0.5  score < CFI)\r\n- The min(1, freq/120) term penalizes high-frequency tokens\r\n\r\n**Revised Formula Analysis:**\r\n- \"for next instantiation\" (freq=160, CFI=1.00): score = 1.0 x min(1, 160/120) = 1.0 x 1.0 = 1.0\r\n- \"Phase 1\" (freq=136, CFI=0.96): score = 0.96 x min(1, 136/120) = 0.96 x 1.0 = 0.96\r\n- \"temporal\" (freq=40, CFI=0.70): score = 0.70 x min(1, 40/120) = 0.70 x 0.33 = 0.23\r\n\r\n**Problem:** The min(1, x) saturates at freq=120. Need different penalty function.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Revised Scoring Function\r\n**score(T) = CFI(T) x freq_penalty(T)**\r\n\r\nWhere:\r\n```\r\nfreq_penalty(T) = {\r\n    0.0                    if freq(T) < 3      (noise)\r\n    freq(T) / 120          if 3 � freq(T) < 120  (normal range)\r\n    1.0                    if freq(T) � 120     (capped)\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior:**\r\n- Constant format (freq=160, CFI=1.00): score = 1.0 x 1.0 = 1.0  Still wrong!\r\n- Need INVERSE penalty for high frequency\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Final Scoring Function\r\n**score(T) = CFI(T) x log(1 + freq(T)) / log(121)**\r\n\r\nThis normalizes frequency to [0, 1] log scale:\r\n- freq=1: score = CFI x log(2)/log(121) � CFI x 0.09\r\n- freq=120: score = CFI x log(121)/log(121) = CFI x 1.0\r\n- freq=160: score = CFI x log(161)/log(121) � CFI x 1.11 (clamped to 1.0)\r\n\r\n**Still problematic for constant tokens.**\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Alternative: Binary Frequency Cap\r\n**score(T) = CFI(T) if freq(T) < 120 ELSE CFI(T) x 0.1**\r\n\r\nThis penalizes tokens appearing in 75%+ of pulses by 10x.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Experiment Design\r\n\r\n### Test Corpus\r\n- 200 pulses (same as Strategy A/B)\r\n- Token corpus: all unique tokens from pulses\r\n\r\n### Metrics\r\n1. **Precision@K**: Among top-K tokens, what fraction are \"research trajectory\" vs \"constant format\"?\r\n2. **Recall@K**: Do we capture the actual research tokens?\r\n3. **F1 Score**: Balance precision vs recall\r\n\r\n### Baseline Comparison\r\n- Strategy A (CFI � 0.7): precision=0.5653, recall=0.071\r\n- Strategy B (CFI � 0.5 AND freq ? [3, 120)): Expected improvement\r\n\r\n### Execution\r\n```powershell\r\n# For each token T:\r\n$logFreqFactor = [Math]::Log(1 + $freq) / [Math]::Log(121)\r\n$score = $CFI * $logFreqFactor\r\nif ($\r\n\r\n## For Next Instantiation\r\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\r\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 15:58:41","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774382325535}}
